f(x) = \cosh(x)
f(x)=\cosh (x)-1-\frac{x^2}2
\cosh (x) \leq 1 + \frac{x^2}{2}
f(x) = \cosh (x)
x_0 \in [0,x]
f'(x_0) = \frac{f(x) - f(0)}{x - 0}.
f(x) = \cosh (x) \implies f'(x) = \sinh (x)
\sinh (x_0) \geq x_0
1) \,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,f(x) = \cosh (x) = \cosh (x)
2) \,\,\,\,\,\,\,\, \,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\, f(0) = \cosh (0) = 1
3) \,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\, \, x - 0 = x.
\sinh (x_0) = \frac{\cosh (x) - 1}{x}.
\sinh (x_0) \geq x_0
x_0 \leq \frac{\cosh (x) - 1}{x}
x \cdot x_0 \leq \cosh (x) - 1
\implies \cosh(x) \geq 1 + x \cdot x_0.
