\int_{0}^{x}{f(t)dt}=e^{x}-e^{-x} \ge 2x
\int_{0}^{x}{\left(\int_{0}^{u}{f(t)dt}\right)du}=\boxed{e^{x}+e^{-x} -2\ge x^2} 
\implies \boxed{\boxed{\cosh{x}\ge 1+\frac{x^2}{2}}}
